04645nam a22007455i 9783110753073DE-B159720211027022714.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||211027t20212021gw     fo  d z      eng d  a2021945471  a97831107530737 a10.1515/97831107530732doi  a(DE-B1597)584734  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  agwcDE 7aLAN0090002bisacsh1 aCorreia Saavedra, David, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aMeasurements of Grammaticalization :bDeveloping a Quantitative Index for the Study of Grammatical Change /cDavid Correia Saavedra. 1aBerlin ;aBoston : bDe Gruyter Mouton, c[2021] 4cÂ©2021  a1 online resource (XII, 246 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aTrends in Linguistics. Studies and Monographs [TiLSM] ,x1861-4302 ;v36600tFrontmatter -- tAcknowledgements -- tContents -- tWhy did I write this book? -- t1 Introduction -- t2 Theoretical background -- t3 Grammaticalization parameters quantified -- t4 Data and methods -- t5 Quantifying grammaticalization in synchrony -- t6 Diachronic study -- t7 Conclusions -- tReferences -- tAppendices -- tAppendix A Database -- tAppendix B Random samples for classification data (chapter 6) -- tAppendix C Additional figures (chapter 6) -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aGrammaticalization has often been described as a gradual phenomenon. While many studies have discussed the quantitative aspects of grammaticalization, there has been little to no work that has tried to propose a way of measuring degrees of grammaticalization. This book addresses this gap by proposing a corpus-based approach to the measurement of grammaticalization, using binary logistic regression modelling. Such an approach has theoretical benefits as it can provide empirical evidence for the gradience and gradualness of grammaticalization. It can help substantiate observations that have been done on the basis of case studies so far, such as the hypothesized unidirectionality of grammaticalization. In addition, as the methods proposed in this book rely on corpus-based data only, it offers a way of comparing grammaticalization across multiple languages, which is currently a challenging endeavour. What this book hopes to achieve is to start a discussion on the measurement of grammaticalization. To draw a parallel, the field of morphological productivity has greatly benefited from the discussions (and disputes) regarding how its object of study should be measured, and I believe that so will the field of grammaticalization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 4aGrammatikalisierung. 4aKonstruktionsgrammatik.  aGradience.  aGradualness.  aGrammaticalization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021 Englishz978311075411708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021z9783110753882oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831107531650 cprintz978311075294640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311075307340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110753073423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110753073/original  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075411-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aZDB-23-DSPb2021